html.body: ONTOX_LB0004_001 Gene regulatory network for bile acid biosynthesis and metabolism Gene regulatory network created using the TF-maps script (in house script) to construct SBGN Activity Flow networks using the TRRUST v2 dataset on transcription factors and target genes. Curator: Luiz Ladeira, Biomechanics Research Unit, GIGA In Silico Medicine, University of Liège - Liège, Belgium. Contact: lcladeira@uliege.be Sources: Han, H., Cho, J.-W., Lee, S., Yun, A., Kim, H., Bae, D., Yang, S., Kim, C. Y., Lee, M., Kim, E., Lee, S., Kang, B., Jeong, D., Kim, Y., Jeon, H.-N., Jung, H., Nam, S., Chung, M., Kim, J.-H., and Lee, I. (2018). TRRUST v2: An expanded reference database of human and mouse transcriptional regulatory interactions. Nucleic Acids Research, 46(D1), D380–D386. https://doi.org/10.1093/nar/gkx1013
